<section class="content-section">  
  <h2>secure?</h2>
  <h3 class="section-description"><strong>Prompt injection</strong> isn’t an <strong>LLM</strong> problem,<br> it’s an <strong>infrastructure</strong> problem.</h3>
  
  <div class="container security-more">
    <p>Other tools yell at the model and hope it behaves.<br/>
    <strong>mlld</strong> enforces policy at the runtime level.</p>
    <p>Data gets labeled, guards fire on tainted data.<br/>
    The LLM doesn’t get a vote and isn’t asked to guess.</p>
    <p>No magic. No proprietary security pixie dust. Just classic security principles and <strong>you</strong> doing the work of knowing your data and taking responsibility to secure it.</p>
    <p>From the cocreator of <strong>npm audit</strong> and <strong>Code4rena</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

